  "storyline": "# Storyline\n\n## Context\n\nRegional crime patterns track socio-economic conditions, but policy conversations needed a defensible, quantitative link rather than anecdote.\n\n## Workflow\n\nEDA on socio-economic indicators → interaction-term feature engineering → regression modeling → PCA variable extraction → policy-style interpretation.\n\n## Technical Implementation\n\n- **Analysis:** 10K+ crime records with Pandas/NumPy, correlating unemployment, education and income.\n- **Features:** log transforms and 2 interaction terms (+10% model fit) capturing compound effects.\n- **Modeling:** Multivariate Linear Regression with R² ≈ 0.78; PCA isolated 6 key driving variables.\n\n## Outcomes\n\nDistilled outputs into 6-variable summaries supporting a policy-style interpretation of socio-economic drivers, grounded in quantitative evidence."
